---
title: Pan-Fried Teriyaki Salmon with Jasmine Rice and Roasted Broccoli
description: Widely used in Japanese barbecue dishes, teriyaki's name comes from the Japanese 'teri', meaning 'shine' and 'yaki' meaning fried or grilled. Reduce down the sauce in the pan after frying the fish to turn it into a sticky glaze, whilst broccoli, spring onion and zesty rice give freshness.
